Author: authpaperICO
Title: [ANN][ICO] Authpaper Coin – deliver secrets with trust and verify
Body: For anyone who don't understand how the referral works, here is an example:  Suppose Alice registers this program with referral from Bob. If Bob does not have referral from anyone when register, Alice can buy AUPC at price 0.001 * 95% = 0.00095 ether. If Bob has referral from Charles, who also has referral from Dennis and so on up to the seventh referral, Alice will have 5 + 3 + 2 + 4 * 1 = 14% discount. She can buy AUPC in 0.00086 ether.  Now further suppose Alice has paid 0.86 ether and received 1000 AUPC. Bob will receive 100 AUPC and 0.043 ether as present, Charles will have 60 AUPC and 0.0258 ether, and Dennis will have 40 AUPC and 0.0172 ether.

Author: authpaperICO
Title: [ANN][ICO] Authpaper Coin – deliver secrets with trust and verify
Body: It happens all the time in business world. For example, a business need to present the delivery record of trading documents when they are asking loan from a bank for a purchase order. If a company has a lot of trading business, they need to present all the delivery record when auditing. This proves the trading orders are done. For legal, forensic investigations and accounting firms, everything they send out requires a delivery record, in order to prove where the document / material has gone and who has access the data during the delivery.  In Hong Kong, if you have a civil dispute and need to be solved via the judiciary system, you need to send a copy of your statement and evidence to another party and present the record to the count. If you fail to prove that you have sent the materials to another party, you will loss the dispute right away.  Public delivery records also benefit in personal usage, if you are sending the record to multiple parties, you can always check how many parties have received the data and how many have not.  These examples also show the potential clients of the platform.

Author: authpaperICO
Title: [ANN][ICO] Authpaper Coin – deliver secrets with trust and verify
Body: When a peer (e.g. Alice) would like to send out a data to another (e.g. Bob), she will need to sign a smart contract with some peers (mailers) so that mailers will do it for Alice. The smart contract will be stored on blockchain and mailers will ask more peers to help. After the data is delivered and Bob send out a signed delivery record to the smart contract. The smart contract executes accordingly to transfer stamps, currency of the platform, to the mailers for their services, and issue new stamps to helping peers. So we need smart contract here. The smart contract is different from other smart contract you have seen, because smart contract in our platform accepts attachments (delivery records, magnet link of the data, etc). Hence we need a custom built blockchain. We will provide a set of standard smart contract with the platform, so users only need to pick a contract they want and execute.

Author: authpaperICO
Title: [ANN][ICO] Authpaper Coin – deliver secrets with trust and verify
Body: Yes, it is legally accepted as long as you have proper delivery record. That's why there are some electronic document delivery service already using centralized servers. The problem here is current competitors use centralized servers and require users to upload their documents / data in plain-text. The users want to keep things confidential so go back the old method. Our platform is designed to solve exactly this issue. This platform allows users to keep everything secret, while providing a unforgeable delivery record. It is P2P so even us cannot change things on blockchain, so it is really unforgeable.

Author: authpaperICO
Title: [ANN][ICO] Authpaper Coin – deliver secrets with trust and verify
Body: BitTorrent handles the actual data flow. In this platform, blockchain is like a post board, showing all delivery requests and delivery records and everyone token balances. When a peer would like to assist a data delivery request, it join the corresponding swarm to download and share the data pieces (all are encrypted). This part is the BitTorrent part. When the delivery is done, the delivery record is posted on blockchain. The peers will be awarded tokens according his contribution on delivering data inside the swarm.

Author: authpaperICO
Title: [ANN][ICO] Authpaper Coin – deliver secrets with trust and verify
Body: WEBSITE | TWITTER | MEDIUM |WHITEPAPER | TELEGRAM | Bounty  ICO LIVE   Delivery of confidential and commercial documents have relied on physical mailing in the previous decades. Physical mailing allows documents to be delivered confidentially with concrete evidence on delivering / not delivering and current digital delivery solutions failed to do so. However, it is well-known that all printed documents/ credentials are potentially subject to forgery. Every year, billions USD has lost directly due to document fraud. On the other hand, whenever there is a need to deliver or broadcast a huge amount of digital data, like a game, operating system, or movie, data integrity often cannot be guaranteed. Also, it requires a very stable connection for a long time between senders and receivers or between a huge server and receivers. In many cases, people will simply copy the data into a storage medium like DVD, USB Drive, or a hard disk, and mail it to the recipient. BitTorrent (BT) seems to be the answer to these problems. However, it cannot provide an incentive for peers to deliver a data which is confidential to them, and it cannot provide an unforgeable record of delivering or attempt to deliver data to someone. Here is what Blockchain can help. Combining Blockchain and BT to provide a peer-to-peer platform which encourages peers to deliver confidential data for others is the core concept of Authpaper Delivery platform. This platform also supports certifying the source of a data and circulating a data for approval.    This platform provides a lot of impacts across multiple industries. No matter legal, accounting, trading, commercial parties benefit a lot by saving the printing and mailing cost and time. It also helps in solving the copyright data leakage problem. Data issuer can create multiple copies of data with different watermarks and keep it on this platform before selling to others. Delivering system images across the network becomes handy as both parties do not need to be online together.  We have issued an ERC-20 based coin, Authpaper Coin (AUPC) and distribute to the supporters and partners. With AUPC, you can 1) When the platform is ready, AUPC will be exchanged to the token of the platform 2) Spent on us or our partners for services (We are preparing, will publish on ICO website when ready.) 3) Exchange on exchanges (Still applying, will publish on our channels when done)  Token Standard: ERC-20 Token Amount: 400,000,000 Token sale price: 0.001 ETH Up to 15% discount if register with referrer !  Goal: 250,000 ETH Soft cap: 25,000 ETH ICO start date: 10th Mar 2019 ICO end date: 15th Aug 2019   Airdrop: Free 100 AUPC 1) Register our online service here: https://authpaper.com/login.php    2) Email to contact@authpaper.com by the Google account login to our service with title “Withdraw AUPC” and content your ERC-20 address.  With our AUPC token on hand, want to earn more ETH and AUPC? Join our marketing reward program! 1) Register on https://authpaper.io/buyingcoin 2) Promote this project to others and asks others to register and purchase AUPC with your user name as referral 3) They enjoy discount because of your referral, you get reward automatically by smart contract ! First level referral 10% AUPC + 5% ETH Second level 6% AUPC + 3% ETH Third level 4% AUPC + 2% ETH Purchaser also gets discount as having a referral. First level brings 5%, second level extra 3%, third level extra 2%. Each additional level brings extra 1%. Max discount is 15% (8 levels).  All token distributions and bonuses are sent out immediately by smart contract !  Caution: You need to make sure you are legal to purchase AUPC before really purchasing. So far we know purchasing token from China and USA citizens are not allowed.

Author: authpaperICO
Title: [ANN][ICO] Authpaper Coin – deliver secrets with trust and verify
Body: One thing people should be notified is that the token we are offering in this ICO is an ERC-20 token, Authpaper Coin (AUPC). As Authpaper Delivery platform requires a customized blockchain, the coin cannot be used directly on it. Once the platform is ready, we will provide an offer to exchange the coins with Authpaper stamp, the currency in the platform, at a certain rate. Coin holders can also trade the coins on public exchanges or use it to redeem other services from us.  Authpaper Limited provides customized solutions for companies to issue public verifiable certificates and coupons. Currently the products are integrated inside the clients’ systems and not available to the public. But we will release a public version of certificate issuing system and coupon solution during the development of the Authpaper Delivery platform for coin redemptions. We and our partner companies also provide computer and mobile forensic investigations, security risk assessments, and consultant services, mainly in Hong Kong. Authpaper coins can also be used to redeem discounts for these services. The list of company accepting Authpaper coin for discount, services they provide, and contact will be listed on the ICO website.  To make sure the investors will not be harmed by speculators due to the price fluctuations of AUPC. A lockup period is introduced. Only 8*N% of the AUPC an investor bought during the ICO period can be transferred to others before 15th September 2019. N is number of months after 15th September 2018, the ICO launch date. It means for 100 AUPC bought during ICO, only 8% can be traded from 15th September 2018 to 15th October 2018, 16% from 15th October to 15th November, and so on. After 31st September 2019, all AUPC are tradable. AUPC paying for Authpaper services and bought from public exchanges do not have such limitation.
